The context is a very high overview of  spring MVC is designed with Front Controller design pattern where Dispatcher servlet will receive all the requests and invoke the corresponding handler so that your controller method is called is your controller class is annotated with 
@Controller annoation dispatcher servlet considered that return value and try to locate View in your MVC so that you need to configure any one of implementations of ViewResolver in your case you need to configure InternalResourceViewResolver and Themeleaf with corresponding view locations.

if your controllers is annotated with @RestController return value of the handler will be as considered as Http response Dispatcher servlet will not look any views(it will considered return value  as http response body)

you can achieve same thing with @Controller annotation itself simple add this annoation @ResponseBody in your handler method(return value is considered as http response).

The @RestController annotation in Spring MVC is nothing but a combination of @Controller and @ResponseBody annotation. It was added into Spring 4.0 to make the development of RESTful Web Services in Spring framework easier.

The job of @Controller is to create a Map of model object and find a view but @RestController simply return the object and object data is directly written into HTTP response as JSON or XML.

    @SuppressWarnings({})
    @RestController
    public class TestController {
    	@PostMapping(&quot;/test/1&quot;)
    	public Object Test1(@RequestBody HashMap&lt;String, String&gt; obj) throws ParseException, IOException {
    		return null;
    	}

Read more: https://javarevisited.blogspot.com/2017/08/difference-between-restcontroller-and-controller-annotations-spring-mvc-rest.html#ixzz62Jw1WOs3

@RestController is combination of @Controller and @ResponseBody.So request handling method returns objects into HttpResponse as Json or XML, therefore @ResponseBody isn&#39;t required.

```
@RestController
public class UserRestController { }

@Controller
@ResponseBody
public class UserController { }
```

@ResponseBody is a Spring annotation which binds a method which return value to web response body.It tells a controller that the object returned is automatically serialized into JSON and passed back into the HttpResponse object.

